Sharing keys is hard
Using a trusted third party makes key exchange much easier.

Replay Attack
- Eve records a message and replays it later.

Session Key reuse
- Eve replays message from Alice to Bob, so Bob re-uses session key

Protocols must provide authentication and defend against replay

Needham-Schroeder

Message for Bob with R1
Alice --Alice||Bob||R1--> Cathy

Alice <--{Alice||Bob||R1||k_s{Alice||k_s}k_B}k_A-- Cathy

Alice --{Alice||k_s}k_B--> Bob

Alice <--{R2}k_s-- Bob

Alice --{R2-1}k_s--> Bob

Numbers Used Only Once
NONCE

